    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stone documents used as records of land grants to vassals by the Kassites in Babylonia between the 16th and the 12th century BCE. Akkadian for "boundary," the original stone would be kept in a temple and a clay copy, which was used as a boundary marker.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
